<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brischke" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Blennocampa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blennocampa brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">Blennocampa brevicornis</taxonomicName>
Brischke, 1883: 282-283. ♀. Syntypes (assumed). Type locality: Poland [
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Westpreußen”">&quot;Westpreussen&quot;</normalizedToken>
= western Prussia]. Types probably lost (
<bibRefCitation author="Blank, SM" editor="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="141 - 174" refId="B17" refString="Blank, SM, Taeger, A, 1998. Comments on the taxonomy of Symphyta (Hymenoptera) (Preliminary studies for a catalogue of Symphyta, part 4). In: Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Eds., Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 141 - 174" title="Comments on the taxonomy of Symphyta (Hymenoptera) (Preliminary studies for a catalogue of Symphyta, part 4)." volumeTitle="Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta)." year="1998">Blank and Taeger 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Blennocampa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blennocampa puncticeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticeps">Blennocampa puncticeps</taxonomicName>
Konow, 1886a: 215-216. ♀, ♂. Syntypes. Type locality: Switzerland, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Zürich">Zuerich</normalizedToken>
. Lectotype ♀ (SDEI) designated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" author="Koch, F" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="311 - 330" refId="B81" refString="Koch, F, 1988. Die Gattung Claremontia Rohwer (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 35 (4-5): 311 - 330, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" title="Die Gattung Claremontia Rohwer (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" volume="35" year="1988">Koch (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. Treated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" author="Koch, F" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="311 - 330" refId="B81" refString="Koch, F, 1988. Die Gattung Claremontia Rohwer (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 35 (4-5): 311 - 330, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" title="Die Gattung Claremontia Rohwer (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" volume="35" year="1988">Koch (1988)</bibRefCitation>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Konow" baseAuthorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Claremontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Claremontia confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa">Claremontia confusa</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Monophadnoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monophadnoides puncticeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticeps">Monophadnoides puncticeps</taxonomicName>
: Benson, 1952; treated as species distinct from 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="confusa">M. confusa</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Poterium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poterium sanguisorba" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sanguisorba">Poterium sanguisorba</taxonomicName>
[currently 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Sanguisorba" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sanguisorba minor" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">Sanguisorba minor</taxonomicName>
] recorded as host of larva. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chambers, VH" journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Monthly Magazine" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B32" refString="Chambers, VH, 1961. Bedfordshire sawflies: with some new food-plants. The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 96(21)[1960]: 209-211." title="Bedfordshire sawflies: with some new food-plants. The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 96 (21) [1960]: 209 - 211." year="1961">Chambers (1961)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Potentilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Potentilla reptans" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">Potentilla reptans</taxonomicName>
recorded as host of larva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
ZMUO specimens, from Finland, are not reared; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Sanguisorba" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sanguisorba" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Sanguisorba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, recorded as a host plant by 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B10" refString="Benson, RB, 1952. Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6(2b): 51-137." title="Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6 (2 b): 51 - 137." year="1952">Benson (1952)</bibRefCitation>
, can be excluded as a possible host plant at these localities, but 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Potentilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Potentilla erecta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erecta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Potentilla erecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is present in abundance at one of the localities in Eastern Finland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.20586" author="Konow, FW" journalOrPublisher="Wiener entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="211 - 218" refId="B84" refString="Konow, FW, 1886a. Die europaeischen Blennocampen (soweit dieselben bisher bekannt sind). Wiener entomologische Zeitung 5 (6): 211 - 218, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.20586" title="Die europaeischen Blennocampen (soweit dieselben bisher bekannt sind)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.20586" volume="5" year="1886 a">Konow (1886a)</bibRefCitation>
, in a key, described the tibiae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Konow" baseAuthorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Claremontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Claremontia confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Claremontia confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Blennocampa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blennocampa confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Blennocampa confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as mainly black with only the knees very narrowly whitish and the protibia only whitish on the anterior face, and wrote that the tibiae of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. puncticeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="puncticeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. puncticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were mainly pale. 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B10" refString="Benson, RB, 1952. Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6(2b): 51-137." title="Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6 (2 b): 51 - 137." year="1952">Benson (1952)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacourt, J" journalOrPublisher="Editions, Verrieres-le-Buisson" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B106" refString="Lacourt, J, 2020. Symphytes d'Europe. Hymenopteres d'Europe 2. N. A. P. Editions, Verrieres-le-Buisson" title="Symphytes d'Europe. Hymenopteres d'Europe 2. N. A. P." year="2020">Lacourt (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, among others, distinguished 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brischke" baseAuthorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Claremontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Claremontia brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Claremontia brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Konow" baseAuthorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Claremontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Claremontia confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Claremontia confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. puncticeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="puncticeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. puncticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using several characters, also including the color of the metatibia of females. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brischke, CGA" journalOrPublisher="Ecological Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B24" refString="Brischke, CGA, 1883. Beobachtungen ueber die Arten der Blatt- und Holzwespen von C. G. A. Brischke, Hauptlehrer a. D. in Langfuhr und Dr. Gustav Zaddach weiland Professor in Koenigsberg. Zweite Abtheilung. Schriften der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Danzig, N. S. 5[1881-1883](4): 201-328." title="Beobachtungen ueber die Arten der Blatt- und Holzwespen von C. G. A. Brischke, Hauptlehrer a. D. in Langfuhr und Dr. Gustav Zaddach weiland Professor in Koenigsberg. Zweite Abtheilung. Schriften der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Danzig, N. S. 5 [1881 - 1883] (4): 201 - 328." year="1883">Brischke (1883)</bibRefCitation>
described the metatibia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brischke" baseAuthorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Claremontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Claremontia brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Claremontia brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a nominal species not known to 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.20586" author="Konow, FW" journalOrPublisher="Wiener entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="211 - 218" refId="B84" refString="Konow, FW, 1886a. Die europaeischen Blennocampen (soweit dieselben bisher bekannt sind). Wiener entomologische Zeitung 5 (6): 211 - 218, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.20586" title="Die europaeischen Blennocampen (soweit dieselben bisher bekannt sind)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.20586" volume="5" year="1886 a">Konow (1886a)</bibRefCitation>
, as extensively yellow-white. Numerous barcoded females (SDEI, ZMUO) belong to two separate COI sequence clusters (distance 3.1-5.8%), which correlate fully with their leg color. Accordingly, we think that the original description of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to what has more recently come to be known as 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. puncticeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="puncticeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. puncticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that the correct name for the other species is 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unlike some previous authors, we did not detect a clear difference in the sculpture of the head of the two forms. Distinction of the males is problematic, because of the lack of reliably identified male specimens of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B10" refString="Benson, RB, 1952. Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6(2b): 51-137." title="Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6 (2 b): 51 - 137." year="1952">Benson (1952)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;is entirely parthenogenetic, at least in Britain&quot;. On the other hand, several male specimens of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. A. Claremontia confusa (Konow, 1886). Dorsal habitus ♀ (ZMUO. 044470); B, C. Claremontia brevicornis (Brischke, 1883), dorsal habitus; B. ♀ (ZMUO. 039550); C. ♂ (ZMUO. 031990)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719518" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">7C</figureCitation>
) have been barcoded, and can thus definitely be associated with that species. Based mainly on barcode-sequenced specimens in ZMUO, females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Konow" baseAuthorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Claremontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Claremontia confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Claremontia confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be separated as follows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<table inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<tr pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<td colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rowspan="1">1</td>
<td colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rowspan="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">a</emphasis>
Length of antenna subequal to length of costa (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. A. Claremontia confusa (Konow, 1886). Dorsal habitus ♀ (ZMUO. 044470); B, C. Claremontia brevicornis (Brischke, 1883), dorsal habitus; B. ♀ (ZMUO. 039550); C. ♂ (ZMUO. 031990)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719518" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">7A</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">b</emphasis>
Metatibia completely black, or with base narrowly pale (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. A. Claremontia confusa (Konow, 1886). Dorsal habitus ♀ (ZMUO. 044470); B, C. Claremontia brevicornis (Brischke, 1883), dorsal habitus; B. ♀ (ZMUO. 039550); C. ♂ (ZMUO. 031990)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719518" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">7A</figureCitation>
) [More robust body shape and slightly darker wings]
</td>
<td colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rowspan="1">
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Konow, 1886)
</td>
</tr>
<tr pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<td colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rowspan="1">-</td>
<td colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rowspan="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">aa</emphasis>
Antenna approximately 0.65-0.80 as long as costa (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. A. Claremontia confusa (Konow, 1886). Dorsal habitus ♀ (ZMUO. 044470); B, C. Claremontia brevicornis (Brischke, 1883), dorsal habitus; B. ♀ (ZMUO. 039550); C. ♂ (ZMUO. 031990)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719518" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">7B</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">bb</emphasis>
Metatibia usually extensively pale, with at least base whitish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. A. Claremontia confusa (Konow, 1886). Dorsal habitus ♀ (ZMUO. 044470); B, C. Claremontia brevicornis (Brischke, 1883), dorsal habitus; B. ♀ (ZMUO. 039550); C. ♂ (ZMUO. 031990)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719518" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">7B</figureCitation>
) [More slender body shape and slightly paler wings]
</td>
<td colspan="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rowspan="1">
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Brischke, 1883)
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
